02 2:27:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladin Range items from ME</span><hr size=1> -Goranga Idol (crappy one)<br>Off a Goranga Gatherer<br>Everywhere<br><br>-Grodan's Idol<br>a Coterie Legionaire (sp?) or a Coterie Centurion<br>6 spawns of these... 2 little houses, each with 3, if you follow the right wall from DSP you will see them<br><br>-Idol of the Fallen<br>Xi Thall<br>spawns in the house, on the lake with all the Xi Xau's, Xin Thall Centiens, and Xi Vius'.<br><br>Grodan's Idol drop rate seems to be nerfed a bit, used to be able to get it after 20-30min of killing them, haven't seen one (but heard of them dropping, after being given away hehe) since I got mine about a month after luclin was released.<br>Xi Thall will take atleast one very skilled groups, or two groups with a good puller. He has a LOT of pops around him, sometimes best idea is to levitate into the room where he spawns, Divine Aura to take all the HTs, then run and zone out, meanwhile have a shadowknight or Necromancer do that snare/dot thing... once the pally (prolly you) zones out, the shadowknight or necro can tag Xi Thall back to the group since he is seperated from the crowd of returning mobs. I also reccomend a slower for this fight. <p><html><head><P ALIGN=CENTER><img src="http://pstr-m01.ygpweb.aol.com/data/00C/28/1A/55/38/MRT9ttAZhg1S4cQVHb1nau6A5CRUNFrv0180.jpg"></p><P ALIGN=CENTER><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84161"> Click Here For Profile</a></p></head></html> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaleani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saleani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(