tp://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18353>Hawkline</A><br>Level 55 Knight of Mithaniel Marr<br><A HREF = http://www.eqmachina.com>Deus ex Machina</A></font></p><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Coan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 12:33:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladin Range items from ME</span><hr size=1> Another way to take Xi Thall is to invis in, go stand behind him, target him, DA to get him (and everyone else's attention), the run out and straight up the hill from his house.<br><br>When DA runs out, get CoTH back to your group, heal and invis again, run back to him and root him and get CoTH back to your group.  <br><br>Now everything else should go back into the house other than him - go down and pull him back to your group.<br><br>We've used this method to pull him (and more often his PH) and it's worked quite well for us.<br><br>He's not that tough for being a 60.  We've done him with one pally, one mage, an enchanter and a cleric before.<br><br>Good luck on the cloak - he and his PH are on a 34 minute spawn cycle - we went about 3 hours the other day and all we got was PH's. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Coan Bladesworthy<br>Knight of Marr<br>Falcon's Pride<br>The Nameless<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=19.topic"> Next 